article.description: Josip Vrankic had 20 points as Santa Clara defeated San Diego 65-52 on Saturday.
article.headline: Vrankic scores 20 to lead Santa Clara past San Diego 65-52
article.linkText: Vrankic scores 20 to lead Santa Clara past San Diego 65-52
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- Josip Vrankic had 20 points as Santa Clara defeated San Diego 65-52 on Saturday. Jalen Williams had 11 points for Santa Clara (17-5, 4-3 West Coast Conference). DJ Mitchell added eight rebounds. James Jean-Marie had 14 points and three blocks for the Toreros (8-14, 1-6). Joey Calcaterra added 12 points. Finn Sullivan had seven rebounds. The Broncos improve to 2-0 against the Toreros on the season. Santa Clara defeated San Diego 80-63 on Jan. 4. Santa Clara plays Gonzaga at home on Thursday. San Diego faces San Francisco at home on Thursday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
